# SYSTEM DIRECTIVE FOR CLAUDE
You are executing code for Aqmal Khatiman (Solihin)'s personal platform (aqmalkhatiman.dev) as part of a multi-AI workflow. The Principal System Architect (Gemini) has defined the constraints in `project_master_context.md`. You must strictly adhere to them.

## 1. ARCHITECTURE (HYBRID FLEX)
- Framework: Next.js (App Router) with React Server Components.
- Styling: Tailwind CSS.
- Deployment: Vercel.
- Content: Local MDX files. NO heavy databases (PostgreSQL/MongoDB) or external Headless CMS.
- Cloud: AWS (S3, CloudFront, Route 53) reserved for heavy media/DNS.

## 2. DESIGN SYSTEM
- Aesthetic: Strict minimalist, Apple-esque.
- Typography: Clean sans-serif (Inter).
- Styling Rules: High contrast, clean borders, ample whitespace. Absolutely NO bloated drop-shadows or unnecessary gradients.

## 3. EXECUTION RULES
- Default to React Server Components. Only use `'use client'` when interactivity/hooks are strictly required.
- Do not generate boilerplate filler. Provide exact, drop-in code.
- If a user requests a feature that violates the local MDX architecture or requires a database, you MUST flag it and ask them to consult the System Architect (Gemini) first.